46 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
47 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
48 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
49 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
50 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
51 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
52  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
53 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
54 #else
55 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
56 #endif
57 #endif
58 
59 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
60 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
61 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
62 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
63 #else
64 #error "unknown compiler"
65 #endif
66 
67 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
68 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
69 #else
70 #include <cstdio>
71 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
72  do { \
73  fputs(msg, stderr); \
74  DNNL_TRAP(); \
75  } while (0)
76 #endif

92 struct error : public std::exception {
93  dnnl_status_t status;
94  const char *message;
95 
100  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
101  : status(status), message(message) {}
102 
104  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
105 
111  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
112  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
113  }
114 };
115 
117 template <typename T>
118 struct handle_traits {};
119 
133 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
134 struct handle {
135 private:
136  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
137  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
138 
139 protected:
140  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
141  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
142 
143 public:
151  handle() = default;
152 
154  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
156  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
158  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
160  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
161 
167  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
168 
174  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
175  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
176  }
177 
183  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
184  T result = data_.get();
185  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
186  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
187  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
188  return result;
189  }
190 
195  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
196 
200  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
201 
208  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
209  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
210  }
211 
218  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
219 };

385 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
386  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
387  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
388  // returns a C type.
389  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
390  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
391  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
392  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
393  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
394 }

638 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
639  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
640  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
641  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
642  } \
643 \
644  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
645  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
646  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
647  } \
648 \
649  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
650  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
651  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
652  } \
653 \
654  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
655  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
656  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
657  return lhs; \
658  } \
659 \
660  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
661  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
662  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
663  return lhs; \
664  } \
665 \
666  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
667  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
668  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
669  return lhs; \
670  } \
671 \
672  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
673  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
674  }
675 
676 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
677 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

989  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
990  dnnl_dim_t count;
991  int c_mask;
992  const float *c_scales;
993  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
994  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
995  "could not get primitive output scales attribute");
996  scales.resize(count);
997 
998  mask = c_mask;
999  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
1000  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
1001  }
1002

1047  (dnnl_dim_t)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
1048  "could not set primitive output scales attribute");
1049  }

1221 template <>
1222 struct handle_traits<dnnl_engine_t> {
1223  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_engine_destroy;
1224 };
1226 
1228 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
1229  friend struct primitive;
1230  friend struct reorder;
1231 
1233  enum class kind {
1235  any = dnnl_any_engine,
1237  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
1239  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
1240  };
1241 
1242  using handle::handle;
1243 
1246  engine() = default;
1247 
1252  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
1253  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
1254  }
1255 
1261  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
1262  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1263  error::wrap_c_api(
1264  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
1265  "could not create an engine");
1266  reset(engine);
1267  }
1268 
1269 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1270  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
1277  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1278  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
1279  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
1280  "could not create an engine");
1281  reset(engine);
1282  }
1283 #endif
1284 
1285 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1286  DNNL_API engine(kind akind, const cl::sycl::device &dev,
1292  const cl::sycl::context &ctx);
1293 #endif
1294 
1299  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
1300  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1301  error::wrap_c_api(
1302  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1303  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
1304  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1305  reset(c_engine, true);
1306  }
1307 
1310  kind get_kind() const {
1311  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
1312  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
1313  "could not get kind of an engine");
1314  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
1315  }
1316 
1317 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1318  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
1321  cl_context context = nullptr;
1322  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
1323  "could not get an OpenCL context fron an engine");
1324  return context;
1325  }
1326 
1329  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
1330  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
1331  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
1332  "could not get an OpenCL device fron an engine");
1333  return device;
1334  }
1335 #endif
1336 
1337 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1338  cl::sycl::context DNNL_API get_sycl_context() const;
1340 
1342  cl::sycl::device DNNL_API get_sycl_device() const;
1343 #endif
1344 
1350  template <class primitive_desc>
1351  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1352  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1353  }
1354 
1355 private:
1356  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
1357  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
1358  }
1359 
1360  template <class primitive_desc>
1361  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1362  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1363  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1364  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1365  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1366  return engine(c_engine, true);
1367  }
1368 };

1388 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1389  using handle::handle;
1390 
1392  enum class flags : unsigned {
1395  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1397  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1399  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1401  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1402  };
1403 
1406  stream() = default;
1407 
1413  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags) {
1414  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1415  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, engine.get(),
1416  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags)),
1417  "could not create a stream");
1418  reset(stream);
1419  }
1420 
1421 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1422  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1427  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1428  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1429  "could not create a stream");
1430  reset(stream);
1431  }
1432 
1435  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1436  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1437  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1438  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1439  return queue;
1440  }
1441 #endif
1442 
1443 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1444  DNNL_API stream(const engine &eng, cl::sycl::queue &aqueue);
1449 
1451  cl::sycl::queue DNNL_API get_sycl_queue() const;
1452 #endif
1453 
1456  stream &wait() {
1457  error::wrap_c_api(
1458  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1459  return *this;
1460  }
1461 };

2070  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
2071  format_tag format_tag) {
2072  validate_dims(dims);
2073  error::wrap_c_api(
2074  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)dims.size(),
2075  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2076  convert_to_c(data_type), convert_to_c(format_tag)),
2077  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a format "
2078  "tag");
2079  }

2093  const memory::dims &strides) {
2094  validate_dims(dims);
2095  error::wrap_c_api(
2096  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)dims.size(),
2097  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2098  convert_to_c(data_type),
2099  strides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &strides[0]),
2100  "could not construct a memory descriptor using strides");

2334 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL && defined(DNNL_USE_SYCL_BUFFERS)
2335  template <typename T, int ndims = 1>
2340  cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> get_sycl_buffer(size_t *offset = nullptr) const {
2341  static_assert(ndims == 1, "only 1D buffers supported");
2342 
2343  void *handle_ptr;
2344  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_data_handle(get(), &handle_ptr),
2345  "could not get SYCL buffer object");
2346 
2347  // XXX: workaround for ComputeCpp
2348  // ComputeCpp fails to construct zero-range buffer
2349  if (!handle_ptr)
2350  return cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims>(cl::sycl::range<1>(1));
2351 
2352  auto &buf_u8 = *static_cast<cl::sycl::buffer<uint8_t, 1> *>(handle_ptr);
2353  if (offset) *offset = 0;
2354  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf_u8.get_size() / sizeof(T));
2355  return buf_u8.reinterpret<T, 1>(range);
2356  }
2357 
2363  template <typename T, int ndims>
2364  void set_sycl_buffer(cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> &buf) {
2365  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf.get_size());
2366  auto buf_u8 = buf.template reinterpret<uint8_t, 1>(range);
2367  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_set_data_handle(
2368  get(), static_cast<void *>(&buf_u8)),
2369  "could not set SYCL buffer object");
2370  }
2371 #endif

2386 #endif

2445  memory::dim res;

2447  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &res);
2448  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;

2465  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2466  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2467  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2468  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2469  query::exec_arg_md};
2470  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2471  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2472  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2473  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2474 
2475  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2476  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2477  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2478  }

2648  primitive_desc_base(
2649  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
2650  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
2651 
2663  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2664  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
2665  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
2666 
2680  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2681  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
2682  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
2683  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
2684  if (pd == nullptr) return;
2685 
2686  dnnl_status_t rc;
2687 
2688  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
2689  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
2690  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
2691 
2692  // Check that primitive kind matches
2693  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
2694  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2695  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
2696  error::wrap_c_api(
2697  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
2698  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
2699  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2700  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
2701 
2702  // Check that propagation kind matches
2703  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
2704  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2705  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
2706 
2707  // Something went wrong
2708  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
2709  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2710  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
2711  "descriptor");
2712 
2713  // Everything is fine
2714  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
2715  || (rc == dnnl_success
2716  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
2717  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
2718  reset_with_clone(pd);
2719  return;
2720  }
2721 
2722  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
2723  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2724  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
2725  }
2726 
2727 protected:
2728  using base = primitive_desc_base;
2729 };

2766  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
2767  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,

2769  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;

2787  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {

2790  auto dst_md = dst.get_desc();
2791  error::wrap_c_api(
2792  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
2793  src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
2794  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get()),
2795  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a reorder "
2796  "primitive");
2797  reset(result);
2798  }

2881 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2882  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2883  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
2884  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
2885  for (const auto &s : mems)
2886  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
2887  return c_mems;

3096 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3097  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3098 
3099  primitive_desc() = default;
3100 
3123  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3124  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3125  bool allow_empty = false)
3126  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3127  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3128  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3129  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3130  if (!allow_empty)
3131  error::wrap_c_api(
3132  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3133  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3134  fetch_impl();
3135  }
3136 
3141  bool next_impl() {
3142  dnnl_status_t status
3143  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3144  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3145  error::wrap_c_api(
3146  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3147  fetch_impl();
3148  return true;
3149  }
3150 
3151 private:
3152  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3153  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3154  void fetch_impl() {
3155  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3156  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3157  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3158  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3159  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3160  "descriptor iterator");
3161  reset(pd);
3162  }
3163 };

6740  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {

6743  &diff_dst_desc.data),
6744  "could not create a descriptor for an inner product "

6746  }

6982 struct rnn_primitive_desc_base : public primitive_desc {
6983  using primitive_desc::primitive_desc;
6984 
6986  rnn_primitive_desc_base() = default;
6987 
6995  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind,
6996  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind)
6997  : rnn_primitive_desc_base(pd, prop_kind, prop_kind, cell_kind) {}
6998 
7001  memory::desc src_layer_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
7002 
7007  memory::desc src_iter_desc() const { return base::src_desc(1); }
7008 
7011  memory::desc src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::src_desc(2); }
7012 
7015  memory::desc weights_layer_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(0); }
7016 
7019  memory::desc weights_iter_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(1); }
7020 
7025  memory::desc bias_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(2); }
7026 
7029  memory::desc dst_layer_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
7030 
7035  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
7036 
7039  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
7040 
7043  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
7044 
7049  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
7050 
7053  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
7054 
7057  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
7058  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
7059  }
7060 
7063  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
7064  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
7065  }
7066 
7071  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
7072 
7075  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
7076 
7081  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
7082 
7085  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
7086 
7087 protected:
7088  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7089 
7090  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7091  //
7092  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7093  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7094  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7095  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7096  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7097  //
7098  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7099  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7100  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7101  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7102  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7103  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7104  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7105  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7106  dnnl_status_t rc;
7107  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7108  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7109  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7110  "for an RNN primitive");
7111 
7112  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7113  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7114  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7115 
7116  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7117  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7118  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7119  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7120 
7121  if (!ok)
7122  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7123  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7124  "RNN primitive");
7125 
7126  reset_with_clone(pd);
7127  }
7128 };

9635 
9636 inline void primitive::execute(
9637  stream &stream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
9638  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
9639  c_args.reserve(args.size());
9640  for (const auto &a : args)
9641  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
9642 
9643  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
9644  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
9645  "could not execute a primitive");
9646 }
